reviews.review_text:
Hult I've never been in this auditorium, but these audience tapes really capture what it must've been like.  Always like these smaller venue shows, such as these and Auditorium Theatre in Chicago.

Of the 3 AUD's posted here, this one seems to be the best, particularly on the low end.  This is a really fine 80's show.

Saturated and distorted Yes... The levels were too high and this source is a no go.

The tetzeli 421 sounds better

All comes back to me now. So many years later i now remember what the feel was like. Although i enojyed every show on this tour some really stood out   Park West and boise.

 that said these were alot of fun the GREAT northwest.  The crowd during this show here was so into it. i remember trying to dance in the isle's only to be told to get back in the row.  That is until the 2nd encore of satisfaction.  that was pure insanty.  we were all up jumping around and siging at the top of our lungs.  similar to east coast shows.  Never again do i recall another west coast show with this much energy.  the music was fun the sound was GREAT hard to capture the feeling on tape.  yet this version here is closest of all.  We were so lucky back then.  Now I look back on life with all the changes we all go threw. having lost many friends on tour to OD and going to jail.  And so many years later losing loved ones.  Always my GG ....  I miss you girl..  jhon
